Reading_List Ethics & Epistemology of AI


Bringsjord, S., & Govindarajulu, N. S. (2018). Artificial Intelligence. Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy. Retrieved April 17, 2022, from https://plato.stanford.edu/archives/sum2020/entries/artificial-intelligence/

Bietti, E. (2019). From Ethics Washing to Ethics Bashing: A View on Tech Ethics from Within Moral Philosophy (SSRN Scholarly Paper No. ID 3513182). Rochester, NY: Social Science Research Network. https://papers.ssrn.com/abstract=3513182. Accessed 21 February 2021

Coeckelbergh, M. (2010). Moral appearances: Emotions, robots, and human morality. 	Ethics and Information Technology, 12(3), 235–241. https://doi.org/10.1007

Europäische Kommission, Generaldirektion Kommunikationsnetze, Inhalte und Technologien, (2020). The Assessment List for Trustworthy Artificial Intelligence (ALTAI) for self-assessment, Publications Office. https://data.europa.eu/doi/10.2759/791819

Johnson, D. G., & Verdicchio, M. (2023). Ethical AI is not about ai. Communications of the ACM, 66(2), 32–34. https://doi.org/10.1145/3576932 

Leonelli, S. (2020). Scientific Research and big data. Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy. Retrieved April 17, 2022, from https://plato.stanford.edu/archives/sum2020/entries/science-big-data/

Morley, J., Elhalal, A., Garcia, F., Kinsey, L., Mokander, J., & Floridi, L. (2021). Ethics as 	a service: A pragmatic operationalisation of ai ethics. SSRN Electronic Journal. 	https://doi.org/10.2139/ssrn.3784238

Müller, V. C. (2020). Ethics of Artificial Intelligence and Robotics. Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy. Retrieved April 17, 2022, from https://plato.stanford.edu/archives/sum2021/entries/ethics-ai/

Nissbaum, H. (2001) How Computer Systems Embody Values, The Profession, pp. 117-119 

Perrigo, B. (2023, January 18). OpenAI used Kenyan workers on less than $2 per hour: Exclusive. Time. Retrieved April 18, 2023, from https://time.com/6247678/openai-chatgpt-kenya-workers/ 

Thomason, R. (2018). Logic and Artificial Intelligence. Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy. Retrieved April 17, 2022, from https://plato.stanford.edu/archives/sum2020/entries/logic-ai/

